result.formatted_address: 14F, Manning House, 38-48 Queen's Road Central, Central, Hong Kong
result.name: the Hive Central

reviews.text: Fantastic location with good vibe and atmosphere. Staff are brilliant and the open air rooftop terrace is brilliant for breaks and phone calls. Highly recommended for anyone who is looking for an office space in Central.

1. Facilities. Basic office facilities are provided, printing machine, shredder, paper trimmer, etc. They have plenty of desks and some offices in Central. Most offices can contain 4-6 ppl.

2. Snacks and drinks. Almonds and energy bars here are just so good and convenient for hivers!!! They offer multiple kinds of drinks including various soft drinks and beers!!! They hold member lunch from time to time and we don't have to pay for the delivery while getting the special discount!!! BTW, coffees are free haha. I love their coffee and fresh milk.

3. Environment and vibe. Most people coming here are freelancers or those who work on their own but for a corporate (e.g. to serve APac market, expansion, etc). 

4. Location. The Hive Central is really easy to locate, so if your role is client-meeting intensive, this place is highly recommended!

5. Services. Two girls over the counter are so nice!! English, Cantonese, and Mandarin!!
Worked there for 2 days while nomading through Hong Kong. Great if you are staying in central hk. Went up to Victoria peak for lunch break.

A fantastic co-working space in central Hong Kong. Friendly staff, nice design and lots of seating (including a huge outdoor terrace). I stopped by for a 1 day pass. It was a bit pricey (300 HKD) but it might be worth it if you plan to spend a full day there. Tea and coffee is included for free.

Comfy chairs, lots of power outlets, plenty of space for making phone calls (either on the terrace or in the dedicated phone booths).
